  <p>Mrs C, 22 years, comes in with 3-day history of high fever, lower abdominal pain, and foul-smelling vaginal discharge after a self-induced abortion. On examination: T 39.5&deg;C, P 118/min, BP 90/60 mmHg, uterus tender, os open, foul discharge. The nurse acts immediately: <em>two large-bore IVs + blood cultures taken &rarr; ampicillin + gentamicin + metronidazole started &rarr; urinary catheter inserted &rarr; IV fluids &rarr; obstetric team called</em>. Four hours later, after antibiotics running, suction evacuation is performed. Her temperature begins to fall the next day. This sequence &mdash; <strong>antibiotics before evacuation</strong> &mdash; prevented her from going into irreversible septic shock.</p>
