  <details><summary>Q2. What is MVA and when is it preferred over medical MTP?</summary><p><strong>MVA (Manual Vacuum Aspiration)</strong> uses a hand-held syringe to create negative pressure and aspirate the products of conception. It is preferred when gestation is <strong>6&ndash;12 weeks</strong>, when medical MTP is contraindicated (asthma, coagulopathy, ectopic), or when rapid evacuation is needed. It is done under paracervical block and takes only 5&ndash;10 minutes.</p></details>
