  <p>Mrs D, 28 weeks pregnant, presents with extreme pallor, severe fatigue, and Hb 5.8 g/dL. She has been eating mostly rice and pulses throughout pregnancy and has not attended ANC before. This is <strong>severe IDA in pregnancy</strong>. The nurse arranges: (1) blood crossmatch; (2) packed red cells 2 units with furosemide cover; (3) IV iron sucrose 200 mg after transfusion; (4) intensive dietary counselling with the dietitian; (5) registration as high-risk; (6) serial Hb every 2 weeks. This case highlights the importance of early ANC registration and IFA supplementation.</p>
