  <details class="test-item"><summary>Q: Why must thiamine be given before dextrose in HG?</summary><strong>A:</strong> Dextrose infusion increases thiamine demand. Giving dextrose in a thiamine-deficient patient can precipitate Wernicke's encephalopathy (acute confusion, ataxia, ophthalmoplegia) &mdash; a preventable but devastating complication.</details>
