  <p class="answer-text">Recognising the early signs and symptoms of PPH is a critical nursing competency, as haemodynamic decompensation can be rapid and life-threatening. In Indian maternity units with limited blood bank access, the nurse midwife must act within minutes &mdash; calling for help, rubbing up the uterus, and establishing IV access &mdash; before the patient enters irreversible shock. Timely recognition and escalation determine survival.</p>
