  <p class="answer-text">Breast problems in the puerperal period are a common reason for early cessation of breastfeeding in India, contributing to suboptimal infant nutrition. Conditions such as engorgement, cracked nipples, mastitis, and breast abscess form a progression that can be largely prevented by correct breastfeeding technique and demand feeding. The nurse midwife's role in early lactation support and education is pivotal for both maternal and neonatal wellbeing.</p>
